(g)  they are members of the same family.
(2)  A person shall be deemed to be members of the same family if—
(a)  they are connected by blood relationship within the fourth degree of
relationship;
(b)  they are married to one another or if one is married to a person who is
connected within the fourth degree of relationship to the other; or
(c)  one has been adopted as the child of the other or as a child of a person
who is within the third degree of relationship to the other.
(3)  A trustee in a settlement is connected with—
(a)  any individual who in relation to the settlement is a settlor;
(b)  any person who is connected with such an individual; and
(c)  a body corporate which is connected with that settlement.
